glosses: To become an informed and cultured person through education.

examples.text: Sadece sen mi kitap okuyup sözlük karıştırıyorsun! Hıh, tekne kazıntısı seni! Biz de mürekkep yaladık zamanında. Şekerlisinden...
examples.translation: Are you the only one who reads books and flips through dictionaries! Huh, you boat shaving, you! We, too, licked ink back in the day. With sugar...

etymology:
From mürekkep (“ink”) + yalamak (“to lick”), literally “to lick ink”, opinions as to its origins vary:
* From the act of licking the tip of a quill to moisten the ink before writing with it,
* From the habit of scribes licking their fingers before rubbing the paper to remove writing errors,
* From a tradition of school-starting children licking a paper with a prayer written on it in ink and coated with sugar.
